A fan of The Simpsons who was banned from watching the popular TV cartoon as a child has broken a world record after getting covered in tattoos of Homer Simpson.

Lee Weir, 27, dubbed his father the 'real-life Ned Flanders' and was not allowed to watch the popular cartoon as head of the household Homer was depicted to be a 'buffoon'.

But father-of-one Mr Weir was so in love with the famous animated sitcom that he had his favourite characters etched on to his skin in ink for life.

