His 41 tattoos earned him the prestigious title of world record holder for having the most tattoos of the same cartoon character tattooed on the body.

Mr Weir, from Auckland, New Zealand, said: 'I was never allowed to watch The Simpsons growing up as my dad was a real-life Ned Flanders.

'He wouldn't let me watch as it depicted the father and the head of the household to be a bafoon.

'But I've always enjoyed watching the show in later life and it feels incredible to be a record breaker.

