'My two-year-old daughter Lucy can point out different Homer tattoos on my arm - her favourite is "baby Homer".

'To have a record for something that is not only cool but also very close to me is just brilliant.

'It hasn't made me a better person but I definitely think it has made me a slightly cooler one.'

The university student said the Homer sleeve took more than 25 hours to complete and that he had to provide dermatologist reports to Guinness World Records officials to prove they were real.

All of his record-breaking tattoos were done by close friend and tattooist Ben Jenkins and was announced as a world record holder on June 5.

 

